The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Kamala Harris during a ceremony to award the Congressional Space Medal of Honor to astronauts Colonel Douglas Hurley and Colonel Robert Behnken. The ceremony took place at the Indian Treaty Room in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. The Vice President recognized the achievements of the astronauts and their contributions to American space exploration. She highlighted their roles in the development of the Crew Dragon spacecraft and their successful mission to the International Space Station. The Vice President also emphasized the importance of collaboration with the private sector in advancing space capabilities. She mentioned the significance of their work in paving the way for future space missions and inspiring the next generation of astronauts. The Vice President concluded by expressing gratitude to the astronauts and their families, and congratulating them on their achievements.